data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType` which combines the type check and cast:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

The generic overload `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(object)` (MSTest v3+) asserts the type **and** returns the typed instance, so you can continue making assertions on it without a manual cast. If the type doesn't match, you get a clear failure message instead of an `InvalidCastException`.
